# purrphp/collection — extension patterns

## Class hierarchy

```
AbstractCollection
├── AbstractList     — ordered list (array_values, numeric keys)
│   ├── AbstractSet  — set (deduplication in constructor)
│   └── ...List / ...NotEmptyList
└── AbstractMap      — associative map (string/int keys)
    └── AbstractMutableMap  — mutable map (ArrayAccess)
```

**When to use which:**
- `AbstractList` — order matters, duplicates are allowed
- `AbstractSet` — unique elements, order does not matter
- `AbstractMap` — key → value, immutable
- `AbstractMutableMap` — key → value with ArrayAccess mutation

## Creating a new collection

### Minimal List

```php
/** @template-extends AbstractList<MyType> */
class MyTypeList extends AbstractList
{
    public function __construct(MyType ...$items)
    {
        parent::__construct($items);
    }
}
```

### NotEmpty variant

```php
class MyTypeNotEmptyList extends MyTypeList
{
    /**
     * @throws \Purr\Collection\Exception\InvalidArgumentException
     */
    public function __construct(MyType ...$items)
    {
        if (!$items) {
            throw new \Purr\Collection\Exception\InvalidArgumentException('Items are empty');
        }
        parent::__construct(...$items);
    }
}
```

## Immutability

All methods returning `static` must create a **new instance**:

```php
// ✅ Correct
return new static(...$filteredItems);

// ❌ Incorrect — mutates $this->collection
$this->collection = $filteredItems;
```

## Psalm annotations (required)

```php
/** @template-extends AbstractList<MyType> */        // for List/Set
/** @template-extends AbstractCollection<string, MyType> */ // for Map
/** @template-implements CollectionInterface<MyType> */ // on interfaces
```

## filterUniqValues in Set classes

To customise deduplication (e.g. by an object field), override:

```php
protected function filterUniqValues(array $items): array
{
    $seen = [];
    return array_filter($items, function ($item) use (&$seen) {
        $key = $item->getId();
        return isset($seen[$key]) ? false : ($seen[$key] = true);
    });
}
```

## Exceptions

Use `Purr\Collection\Exception\InvalidArgumentException` (extends `\InvalidArgumentException`).
